21/09/2004
NEW YORK, United States -- OSCE's chairman-in-office, Bulgarian Foreign Minister Solomon Passy, called for implementation Monday (20 September) of a major infrastructure and development programme in Kosovo and Southeast Europe.
Speaking at a high-level conference at UN headquarters in New York, Passy said economic development is the key factor for political stability in the province and the region.
He also called on all communities in Kosovo, including Serbs, to participate in the 23 October parliamentary elections.
(OSCE Web site - 20/09/04)
